    <hr>

    <h4>Centered Columns</h4>
    <p>Centered columns are placed in the middle of the row. This does not center their content, but centers the grid element itself. This is accomplished by adding a class of <code>large-center</code> or <code>small-center</code> depending on which breakpoint you want the columns to center on. Small versions will carry through all breakpoints it not overridden by a large version. You can center any number of columns you have.</p>

<%= code_example '
<div class="row display">
  <div class="small-3 small-centered columns">3 centered</div>
</div>
<div class="row display">
  <div class="small-6 small-centered columns">6 centered</div>
</div>
<div class="row display">
  <div class="small-9 small-centered columns">9 centered</div>
</div>
<div class="row display">
  <div class="small-11 small-centered columns">11 centered</div>
</div>', :html %>

